    <para id="id1166584054603">The Jetpack was actually a real fully functional device: the Bell Rocket Belt. It was designed for use in the US Army, but was rejected because of its short flying time of 21-22 seconds. Powered by hydrogen peroxide (H<sub>2</sub>O<sub>2</sub>), it could fly about 250 m and reach a maximum altitude of 18 m, going 55 km/h. Despite its impracticality in the real world, the Jetpack made a spectacular debut in <emphasis effect="italics">Thunderball</emphasis>. Although Sean Connery is seen in close-up during the takeoff and landings (<link target-id="id1166597840485"/>), the main flight was actually piloted by Gordon Yeager (<link target-id="id1166595183587"/>) and Bill Suitor (<link target-id="id1166596279698"/>). </para>


